thread.title: Jays claim Invitational title

author: News Tribune
title: Jays claim Invitational title
text:
Share 
POTOSI, Mo. — The Jefferson City Jays won the title at the Potosi Cross Country Invitational, while the Lady Jays came in fifth. 
The Jays racked up a team total of 58 points to win the 17-team event. Ste. Genevieve was second with 89 and Hillsboro was third with 97. 
Saxon Teubner led the Jays placing fourth overall, finising in a time of 16:39. 
Also for the Jays, Jackson Schwartz was fifth (16:43), Cole Biesemeyer was 10th (17:00), Landon Dunlap was 13th (17:04), Brendan Bena was 26th (17:34), Thomas Nield was 29th (17:42) and Josh Sabala was 33rd (17:51). 
In the 11-team girls race, Ste. Genevieve won with 36 points, followed by Fatima with 60. The Lady Jays ended up with 116 points. 
Lindsey Biesemeyer was the top finisher for Jefferson City, coming in 19th in 20:38. 
Also for the Lady Jays, Ryan Esterline was 22nd (20:44), Katie Ruth was 27th (21:08), Brianne Bechtel was 28th (21:10), Syleste Martinez was 29th (21:13), Alivia Bopp was 30th (21:10) and Mackenzie Gourley was 31st (21:19). 
Jefferson City won the JV boys race with 29 points, as Priory was second in the 10-team event with 48. Ben Krause of the Jays won in a time of 17:48. ﻿
